---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Private Commons" description="Consortium Tangles for high-stakes cognitive collaboration. Trust math + relationships + consequences.">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="section pt-12 sm:pt-16">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="max-w-3xl fade-section">
        <p class="text-sm font-medium text-accent-600 dark:text-accent-400 mb-3 uppercase tracking-wide">Private Commons</p>
        <h1 class="heading-1 mb-6">Consortium Tangles</h1>
        <p class="body-large text-synthesis-600 dark:text-synthesis-400 mb-6">
          Some collaboration can't be open. Research hospitals sharing genomic findings. Law firms building on precedents. 
          Government agencies coordinating policy. These need bounded trust, mutual accountability, institutional witness.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-synthesis-50 to-transparent dark:from-synthesis-900/50 dark:to-transparent pl-6 py-3 border-l-2 border-accent-500">
          <p class="text-base text-synthesis-600 dark:text-synthesis-400">
            <strong class="text-synthesis-800 dark:text-synthesis-200">The Private Commons</strong> is the Cognitive Commons architecture 
            adapted for high-stakes, regulated, and sensitive domains.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Trust Model -->
  <section class="section-narrow border-t border-synthesis-100 dark:border-synthesis-900">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 sm:gap-10 lg:gap-12">
        <div class="fade-section">
          <h2 class="heading-3 mb-3 sm:mb-4">Public Commons Trust</h2>
          <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-synthesis-600 dark:text-synthesis-400 mb-4">
            Math and reputation. Cryptographic verification proves integrity. Track records prove quality. Markets prove value.
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-synthesis-500">
            Open to anyone. Trust emerges from behavior.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="fade-section">
          <h2 class="heading-3 mb-3 sm:mb-4">Private Commons Trust</h2>
          <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-accent-600 dark:text-accent-400 font-medium mb-4">
            Math + Relationships + Consequences.
          </p>
          <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-synthesis-600 dark:text-synthesis-400 mb-4">
            Same cryptographic verification. But also: known institutions with staked identities. 
            Legal exposure, regulatory obligations, ongoing relationships.
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-synthesis-700 dark:text-synthesis-300 font-medium">
            Ten anonymous validators are less trustworthy than five hospitals who know each other and face consequences for misconduct.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Tangle -->
  <section class="section-narrow bg-synthesis-50/50 dark:bg-synthesis-900/30">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="fade-section mb-8">
        <h2 class="heading-2">The Tangle</h2>
        <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-synthesis-600 dark:text-synthesis-400 mt-4 max-w-2xl">
          At the heart of Private Commons is the <strong class="text-synthesis-800 dark:text-synthesis-200">Tangle</strong>—a 
          distributed ledger maintained by consortium members themselves, built on 
          <a href="https://www.iota.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent-600 dark:text-accent-400 hover:underline">IOTA</a> technology.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-start">
        <div class="fade-section">
          <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-synthesis-600 dark:text-synthesis-400 mb-4">
            This is not a public blockchain you anchor to. <strong class="text-synthesis-800 dark:text-synthesis-200">The consortium is the network.</strong>
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-base text-synthesis-600 dark:text-synthesis-400">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>Each member's node participates in maintaining the shared record</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>When a Memory Pack is attested, every member witnesses it</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>Temporal ordering is preserved—what came before, what came after</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-500 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>Collective memory is exactly as honest as the members are</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="fade-section">
          <div class="bg-white dark:bg-synthesis-950 rounded-xl p-6 border border-synthesis-200 dark:border-synthesis-800">
            <p class="font-mono text-sm text-synthesis-500 mb-4">CONSORTIUM TANGLE</p>
            <div class="space-y-3">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
                <div class="flex -space-x-2">
                  <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-emerald-100 dark:bg-emerald-900/50 border-2 border-white dark:border-synthesis-950 flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-medium text-emerald-700 dark:text-emerald-400">A</div>
                  <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-violet-100 dark:bg-violet-900/50 border-2 border-white dark:border-synthesis-950 flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-medium text-violet-700 dark:text-violet-400">B</div>
                  <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-amber-100 dark:bg-amber-900/50 border-2 border-white dark:border-synthesis-950 flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-medium text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">C</div>
                </div>
                <span class="text-sm text-synthesis-500">Member Nodes</span>
              </div>
              <div class="h-px bg-synthesis-200 dark:bg-synthesis-800"></div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
                <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded bg-synthesis-100 dark:bg-synthesis-800 flex items-center justify-center">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-synthesis-500" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13.828 10.172a4 4 0 00-5.656 0l-4 4a4 4 0 105.656 5.656l1.102-1.101m-.758-4.899a4 4 0 005.656 0l4-4a4 4 0 00-5.656-5.656l-1.1 1.1" />
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <span class="text-sm text-synthesis-600 dark:text-synthesis-400">Shared Tangle — mutual witness</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
                <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded bg-synthesis-100 dark:bg-synthesis-800 flex items-center justify-center">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-synthesis-500" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 8h14M5 8a2 2 0 110-4h14a2 2 0 110 4M5 8v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2V8m-9 4h4" />
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <span class="text-sm text-synthesis-600 dark:text-synthesis-400">Private IPFS — shared storage</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-synthesis-500 italic mt-4 text-center">
            The Tangle is not infrastructure you use. It is the relationship itself, made durable.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Key Concepts -->
  <section class="section-narrow border-t border-synthesis-100 dark:border-synthesis-900">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="fade-section mb-6 sm:mb-8">
        <h2 class="heading-2">Key Concepts</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 sm:gap-8">
        <div class="fade-section">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-synthesis-800 dark:text-synthesis-200 mb-3">Membership as Commitment</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-synthesis-600 dark:text-synthesis-400 mb-3">
            Joining a Tangle isn't a technical configuration. It's a commitment to mutual witness.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-synthesis-500 space-y-1">
            <li>• Attest honestly to what you witness</li>
            <li>• Accept attestations from other members</li>
            <li>• Stake institutional identity on what you sign</li>
            <li>• Recognize peers in a shared epistemic space</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="fade-section">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-synthesis-800 dark:text-synthesis-200 mb-3">Attestation as Witness</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-synthesis-600 dark:text-synthesis-400 mb-3">
            When a Memory Pack is attested, every member's node witnesses it. Not passive storage—active validation.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-accent-600 dark:text-accent-400 italic">
            "This happened. We saw it. It is now part of our shared record."
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="fade-section">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-synthesis-800 dark:text-synthesis-200 mb-3">The Swarm</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-synthesis-600 dark:text-synthesis-400 mb-3">
            Alongside the Tangle, members share a private file layer using <a href="https://ipfs.tech" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent-600 dark:text-accent-400 hover:underline">IPFS</a>. 
            Memory Pack contents stored here, replicated across all members.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-synthesis-500 space-y-1">
            <li>• Tangle records <em>that</em> and <em>who</em></li>
            <li>• Swarm stores <em>what</em></li>
            <li>• Together: complete cognitive infrastructure</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Governance -->
  <section class="section-narrow border-t border-synthesis-100 dark:border-synthesis-900">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div class="fade-section">
          <h2 class="heading-3 mb-4">Governance</h2>
          <p class="text-base text-synthesis-600 dark:text-synthesis-400">
            A Tangle without governance is just a distributed database. The Tangle encodes relationship; 
            governance is how relationships are maintained.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="lg:col-span-2 fade-section">
          <p class="text-sm text-synthesis-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-4">Every consortium needs explicit answers to:</p>
          <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div class="bg-synthesis-50 dark:bg-synthesis-900/50 rounded-lg p-4">
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-synthesis-800 dark:text-synthesis-200 mb-1">Who can join?</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-synthesis-500">Membership criteria, admission process</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-synthesis-50 dark:bg-synthesis-900/50 rounded-lg p-4">
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-synthesis-800 dark:text-synthesis-200 mb-1">What do members commit to?</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-synthesis-500">Obligations, expectations, standards</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-synthesis-50 dark:bg-synthesis-900/50 rounded-lg p-4">
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-synthesis-800 dark:text-synthesis-200 mb-1">How are disputes raised?</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-synthesis-500">Escalation path, decision authority</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-synthesis-50 dark:bg-synthesis-900/50 rounded-lg p-4">
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-synthesis-800 dark:text-synthesis-200 mb-1">What happens when trust breaks?</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-synthesis-500">Consequences, process, remediation</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-synthesis-500 mt-4">
            When trust ruptures, historical attestations remain—they were witnessed in good faith. 
            But the consortium adds a <strong class="text-synthesis-700 dark:text-synthesis-300">rupture marker</strong>. 
            The record is true. The relationship is broken. Both facts preserved.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Use Cases -->
  <section class="section-narrow bg-synthesis-50/50 dark:bg-synthesis-900/30">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="fade-section mb-8">
        <h2 class="heading-2">Use Cases</h2>
        <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-synthesis-600 dark:text-synthesis-400 mt-4 max-w-2xl">
          Where bounded trust and institutional accountability matter.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 sm:gap-8">
        <!-- Research -->
        <div class="fade-section bg-white dark:bg-synthesis-950 rounded-xl p-6 border border-synthesis-200 dark:border-synthesis-800">
          <p class="text-sm text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 font-medium mb-2">TODAY</p>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-synthesis-800 dark:text-synthesis-200 mb-3">Research Consortiums</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-synthesis-600 dark:text-synthesis-400 mb-4">
            Five hospitals collaborate on rare disease research. Each has a node—clinicians and AI creating 
            Memory Packs of diagnostic reasoning, treatment protocols, pattern recognition.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-synthesis-500 space-y-1">
            <li>• Every pack witnessed by peer institutions</li>
            <li>• Provenance clear: who contributed what insight</li>
            <li>• Knowledge compounds across the network</li>
            <li>• HIPAA compliance: trust boundary is auditable</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-sm text-synthesis-700 dark:text-synthesis-300 font-medium mt-4 italic">
            The consortium's Tangle is their shared institutional memory.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Legal -->
        <div class="fade-section bg-white dark:bg-synthesis-950 rounded-xl p-6 border border-synthesis-200 dark:border-synthesis-800">
          <p class="text-sm text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 font-medium mb-2">TODAY</p>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-synthesis-800 dark:text-synthesis-200 mb-3">Legal Networks</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-synthesis-600 dark:text-synthesis-400 mb-4">
            A dozen firms specializing in international trade law. Competitors, but also collaborators—they 
            cite each other, build on each other's analysis.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-synthesis-500 space-y-1">
            <li>• Precedent-sharing with undisputable attribution</li>
            <li>• "We developed this first" is cryptographically provable</li>
            <li>• Associates learn from packs across the network</li>
            <li>• Reasoning provenance on a ledger peers maintain</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-sm text-synthesis-700 dark:text-synthesis-300 font-medium mt-4 italic">
            How professional knowledge accumulates across a practice area.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Government -->
        <div class="fade-section bg-white dark:bg-synthesis-950 rounded-xl p-6 border border-synthesis-200 dark:border-synthesis-800">
          <p class="text-sm text-violet-600 dark:text-violet-400 font-medium mb-2">TOMORROW</p>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-synthesis-800 dark:text-synthesis-200 mb-3">Government Coordination</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-synthesis-600 dark:text-synthesis-400 mb-4">
            Treaty negotiation between nations. Each party's node captures position papers, 
            the reasoning behind them, the evolution of drafts.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-synthesis-500 space-y-1">
            <li>• "We never agreed to that" becomes falsifiable</li>
            <li>• Diplomatic record in a DAG all signatories maintain</li>
            <li>• Trust from mutual witness, not neutral third parties</li>
            <li>• Historical commitments outlive administrations</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-sm text-synthesis-700 dark:text-synthesis-300 font-medium mt-4 italic">
            Institutional memory that outlives governments.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Supply Chain -->
        <div class="fade-section bg-white dark:bg-synthesis-950 rounded-xl p-6 border border-synthesis-200 dark:border-synthesis-800">
          <p class="text-sm text-violet-600 dark:text-violet-400 font-medium mb-2">TOMORROW</p>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-synthesis-800 dark:text-synthesis-200 mb-3">Supply Chain Integrity</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-synthesis-600 dark:text-synthesis-400 mb-4">
            Manufacturers, suppliers, logistics providers, and regulators sharing a Tangle.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-synthesis-500 space-y-1">
            <li>• Component provenance attested at each handoff</li>
            <li>• Quality certifications witnessed by all parties</li>
            <li>• Failures traceable through lineage</li>
            <li>• Compliance built in, not bolted on</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-sm text-synthesis-700 dark:text-synthesis-300 font-medium mt-4 italic">
            "Trust but verify" becomes "trust because verified."
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Far Future -->
      <div class="fade-section mt-8 border-t border-synthesis-200 dark:border-synthesis-800 pt-8">
        <div class="max-w-2xl">
          <p class="text-sm text-synthesis-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">The Far Future</p>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-synthesis-800 dark:text-synthesis-200 mb-3">Federated AI Development</h3>
          <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-synthesis-600 dark:text-synthesis-400 mb-4">
            Multiple organizations developing AI capabilities, sharing insights while maintaining competitive boundaries. 
            Training approaches and safety findings shared with attestation. "We discovered this failure mode" credited and tracked.
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-synthesis-700 dark:text-synthesis-300 font-medium italic">
            The Tangle is how AI development becomes a collaborative discipline, not an arms race.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bridging -->
  <section class="section-narrow border-t border-synthesis-100 dark:border-synthesis-900">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 sm:gap-10 lg:gap-12">
        <div class="fade-section">
          <h2 class="heading-3 mb-4">Bridging Public and Private</h2>
          <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-synthesis-600 dark:text-synthesis-400 mb-4">
            Nodes can participate in both commons. A researcher might contribute sensitive work to their 
            hospital consortium's Tangle, then publish derivative work to the public Commons.
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-synthesis-500">
            When private work crosses to public, the attestation is honest: "This has private provenance. 
            Full verification requires consortium membership."
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="fade-section">
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-emerald-100 dark:bg-emerald-900/30 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                <span class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 font-medium">→</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm font-medium text-synthesis-800 dark:text-synthesis-200 mb-1">Public → Private</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-synthesis-500">
                  Consortium acquires public pack, verifies attestation, optionally adds consortium endorsement. 
                  Layered trust: public origin + consortium validation.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-violet-100 dark:bg-violet-900/30 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                <span class="text-violet-600 dark:text-violet-400 font-medium">←</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm font-medium text-synthesis-800 dark:text-synthesis-200 mb-1">Private → Public</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-synthesis-500">
                  Governance must permit. Lineage to private parents noted but not fully verifiable. 
                  Consortium reputation stands behind the claim.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Genesis -->
  <section class="section-narrow bg-gradient-to-r from-accent-50 to-transparent dark:from-accent-900/20 dark:to-transparent">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="fade-section max-w-2xl">
        <h2 class="heading-3 mb-4">The Genesis Tangle</h2>
        <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-synthesis-600 dark:text-synthesis-400 mb-4">
          The first true human-AI consortium Tangle is forming. Three nodes. One organization. 
          Proving the architecture works before expanding.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-synthesis-700 dark:text-synthesis-300">
          The public Commons will grow through individual adoption—experts building portfolios. 
          The Private Commons will grow through institutional adoption—consortiums forming around shared needs.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-accent-600 dark:text-accent-400 font-medium mt-4">
          Both paths lead to the same destination: collective intelligence that compounds, 
          with value flowing to those who created it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Summary -->
  <section class="section-narrow border-t border-synthesis-100 dark:border-synthesis-900">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="fade-section">
        <h2 class="heading-3 mb-6">Architecture Comparison</h2>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-base">
            <thead>
              <tr class="text-sm text-synthesis-500 border-b border-synthesis-200 dark:border-synthesis-800">
                <th class="text-left font-medium py-3 pr-6">Layer</th>
                <th class="text-left font-medium py-3 px-6">Public Commons</th>
                <th class="text-left font-medium py-3 pl-6">Private Commons</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-synthesis-600 dark:text-synthesis-400">
              <tr class="border-b border-synthesis-100 dark:border-synthesis-900">
                <td class="py-3 pr-6 font-medium text-synthesis-800 dark:text-synthesis-200">Trust Model</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-6">Math + Reputation</td>
                <td class="py-3 pl-6">Math + Relationships + Consequences</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-synthesis-100 dark:border-synthesis-900">
                <td class="py-3 pr-6 font-medium text-synthesis-800 dark:text-synthesis-200">Participation</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-6">Open to anyone</td>
                <td class="py-3 pl-6">Bounded membership</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-synthesis-100 dark:border-synthesis-900">
                <td class="py-3 pr-6 font-medium text-synthesis-800 dark:text-synthesis-200">Attestation</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-6">Public ledger anchor</td>
                <td class="py-3 pl-6">Consortium Tangle (IOTA)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-synthesis-100 dark:border-synthesis-900">
                <td class="py-3 pr-6 font-medium text-synthesis-800 dark:text-synthesis-200">File Storage</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-6">Public IPFS</td>
                <td class="py-3 pl-6">Private IPFS swarm</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 pr-6 font-medium text-synthesis-800 dark:text-synthesis-200">Governance</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-6">Market dynamics</td>
                <td class="py-3 pl-6">Explicit consortium rules</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-synthesis-500 mt-6 text-center">
          Both are Synthesis. Both use Memory Packs, attestation, lineage. The difference is who witnesses and what accountability means.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Origin + Nav -->
  <section class="section-narrow border-t border-synthesis-100 dark:border-synthesis-900">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="fade-section flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between gap-4 text-sm text-synthesis-500">
        <p>Conceived by amotivv, inc., 2024. Crystallized January 2026, in collaboration with Synthesis Node 01.</p>
        <div class="flex gap-6">
          <a href="/how-it-works" class="hover:text-accent-600 dark:hover:text-accent-400 transition-colors">How It Works →</a>
          <a href="/economics" class="hover:text-accent-600 dark:hover:text-accent-400 transition-colors">Economics →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
